{"parse":{"title":"Lavatorium","pageid":37599184,"revid":787062820,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><div role=\"note\" class=\"hatnote navigation-not-searchable\">Not to be confused with the <a href=\"/wiki/Reredorter\" title=\"Reredorter\">Reredorter</a>, the monastic toilet facilities</div>\n<div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:222px;\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Gloucester_Cathedral_lavatory.JPG\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/f/fb/Gloucester_Cathedral_lavatory.JPG/220px-Gloucester_Cathedral_lavatory.JPG\" width=\"220\" height=\"165\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/f/fb/Gloucester_Cathedral_lavatory.JPG/330px-Gloucester_Cathedral_lavatory.JPG 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/f/fb/Gloucester_Cathedral_lavatory.JPG/440px-Gloucester_Cathedral_lavatory.JPG 2x\" data-file-width=\"3648\" data-file-height=\"2736\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Gloucester_Cathedral_lavatory.JPG\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div>14th-century lavatorium at <a href=\"/wiki/Gloucester_Cathedral\" title=\"Gloucester Cathedral\">Gloucester Cathedral</a></div></div></div>\n<p>A <b>lavatorium</b> (<small><abbr title=\"plural\">pl</abbr>.</small> lavatoria), also <a href=\"/wiki/Anglicization\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Anglicization\">anglicized</a> as <b>laver</b> and <b>lavatory</b>, was the communal washing area in a <a href=\"/wiki/Monastery\" title=\"Monastery\">monastery</a>, particularly in mediaeval abbeys and cathedral <a href=\"/wiki/Cloister\" title=\"Cloister\">cloisters</a>. <a href=\"/wiki/Monk\" title=\"Monk\">Monks</a> were required to wash before meals; thus the lavatorium was typically adjacent to the <a href=\"/wiki/Refectory\" title=\"Refectory\">refectory</a>.\n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><input type=\"checkbox\" role=\"button\" id=\"toctogglecheckbox\" class=\"toctogglecheckbox\" style=\"display:none\" /><div class=\"toctitle\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\"><h2>Contents</h2><span class=\"toctogglespan\"><label class=\"toctogglelabel\" for=\"toctogglecheckbox\"></label></span></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#Description\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Description</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#Gallery\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Gallery</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#See_also\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">See also</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#References\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">References</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Description\">Description</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Lavatorium&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: Description\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"thumb tleft\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:222px;\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Much_Wenlock,_priory_latrines_-_geograph.org.uk_-_1627227.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/2d/Much_Wenlock%2C_priory_latrines_-_geograph.org.uk_-_1627227.jpg/220px-Much_Wenlock%2C_priory_latrines_-_geograph.org.uk_-_1627227.jpg\" width=\"220\" height=\"293\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/2d/Much_Wenlock%2C_priory_latrines_-_geograph.org.uk_-_1627227.jpg/330px-Much_Wenlock%2C_priory_latrines_-_geograph.org.uk_-_1627227.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/2d/Much_Wenlock%2C_priory_latrines_-_geograph.org.uk_-_1627227.jpg/440px-Much_Wenlock%2C_priory_latrines_-_geograph.org.uk_-_1627227.jpg 2x\" data-file-width=\"480\" data-file-height=\"640\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Much_Wenlock,_priory_latrines_-_geograph.org.uk_-_1627227.jpg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div>Ruins of octagonal lavatorium at <a href=\"/wiki/Wenlock_Priory\" title=\"Wenlock Priory\">Wenlock Priory</a></div></div></div>\n<p>All monastic orders required <a href=\"/wiki/Handwashing\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Handwashing\">handwashing</a> before meals. A lavatorium was therefore provided near the refectory,<sup id=\"cite_ref-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> either against one wall of the cloister with a long trench basin, or as a free-standing building with a circular or octagonal basin in the centre.<sup id=\"cite_ref-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> An example of the first type, dating to the 14th century, survives at <a href=\"/wiki/Gloucester_Cathedral\" title=\"Gloucester Cathedral\">Gloucester Cathedral</a>, and has a towel cupboard nearby. At <a href=\"/wiki/Durham_Cathedral\" title=\"Durham Cathedral\">Durham Cathedral</a>, the lavatorium was a square building with a circular basin which was replaced in 1432&#8211;33 with one of marble.<sup id=\"cite_ref-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup> At <a href=\"/wiki/Wenlock_Priory\" title=\"Wenlock Priory\">Wenlock Priory</a>, the octagonal lavatorium, now ruined, was decorated with late-12th-century carved panels including one of Jesus with the apostles at the Sea of Galilee.<sup id=\"cite_ref-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-5\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup> There were sometimes taps;<sup id=\"cite_ref-6\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-6\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup> at Wenlock Priory, the water spouted from animal heads mounted on the central pillar.<sup id=\"cite_ref-7\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-7\">&#91;7&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-8\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-8\">&#91;8&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Running water was supplied in lead pipes, and where there were taps they were bronze, although in most cases in England metal fittings have been removed since the <a href=\"/wiki/Dissolution_of_the_monasteries\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Dissolution of the monasteries\">dissolution of the monasteries</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-9\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-9\">&#91;9&#93;</a></sup> The monks' towels were kept nearby in cupboards called <a href=\"/wiki/Aumbry\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Aumbry\">aumbries</a> (derived from the Latin <i>armarium</i> or from Medieval Latin <i>almarium</i>).<sup id=\"cite_ref-10\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-10\">&#91;10&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-11\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-11\">&#91;11&#93;</a></sup> The Refectorian was responsible for keeping the lavatorium clean and ensuring it contained sand and a <a href=\"/wiki/Sharpening_stone\" title=\"Sharpening stone\">whetstone</a> for the monks to sharpen their knives, and for changing the towels twice a week.<sup id=\"cite_ref-12\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-12\">&#91;12&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<div style=\"clear:both;\"></div>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Gallery\">Gallery</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Lavatorium&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: Gallery\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul class=\"gallery mw-gallery-traditional\">\n\t\t<li class=\"gallerybox\" style=\"width: 155px\"><div style=\"width: 155px\">\n\t\t\t<div class=\"thumb\" style=\"width: 150px;\"><div style=\"margin:30px auto;\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Carving,_Wenlock_Priory.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/a/a1/Carving%2C_Wenlock_Priory.jpg/120px-Carving%2C_Wenlock_Priory.jpg\" width=\"120\" height=\"90\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/a/a1/Carving%2C_Wenlock_Priory.jpg/180px-Carving%2C_Wenlock_Priory.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/a/a1/Carving%2C_Wenlock_Priory.jpg/240px-Carving%2C_Wenlock_Priory.jpg 2x\" data-file-width=\"2048\" data-file-height=\"1536\" /></a></div></div>\n\t\t\t<div class=\"gallerytext\">\n<p>Jesus calling the fishermen; 12th-century carving from lavatorium at Wenlock Priory\n</p>\n\t\t\t</div>\n\t\t</div></li>\n\t\t<li class=\"gallerybox\" style=\"width: 155px\"><div style=\"width: 155px\">\n\t\t\t<div class=\"thumb\" style=\"width: 150px;\"><div style=\"margin:15px auto;\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Carved_arcade_in_the_Lavatorium_-_geograph.org.uk_-_1226728.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/6/69/Carved_arcade_in_the_Lavatorium_-_geograph.org.uk_-_1226728.jpg/90px-Carved_arcade_in_the_Lavatorium_-_geograph.org.uk_-_1226728.jpg\" width=\"90\" height=\"120\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/6/69/Carved_arcade_in_the_Lavatorium_-_geograph.org.uk_-_1226728.jpg/135px-Carved_arcade_in_the_Lavatorium_-_geograph.org.uk_-_1226728.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/6/69/Carved_arcade_in_the_Lavatorium_-_geograph.org.uk_-_1226728.jpg/180px-Carved_arcade_in_the_Lavatorium_-_geograph.org.uk_-_1226728.jpg 2x\" data-file-width=\"480\" data-file-height=\"640\" /></a></div></div>\n\t\t\t<div class=\"gallerytext\">\n<p>Arcade in former lavatorium, <a href=\"/wiki/Kirkham_Priory\" title=\"Kirkham Priory\">Kirkham Priory</a> (12th&#8211;13th century)\n</p>\n\t\t\t</div>\n\t\t</div></li>\n\t\t<li class=\"gallerybox\" style=\"width: 155px\"><div style=\"width: 155px\">\n\t\t\t<div class=\"thumb\" style=\"width: 150px;\"><div style=\"margin:37.5px auto;\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:SintBaafsGent_27-07-2008_16-52-24.JPG\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/b/b4/SintBaafsGent_27-07-2008_16-52-24.JPG/120px-SintBaafsGent_27-07-2008_16-52-24.JPG\" width=\"120\" height=\"75\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/b/b4/SintBaafsGent_27-07-2008_16-52-24.JPG/180px-SintBaafsGent_27-07-2008_16-52-24.JPG 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/b/b4/SintBaafsGent_27-07-2008_16-52-24.JPG/240px-SintBaafsGent_27-07-2008_16-52-24.JPG 2x\" data-file-width=\"1593\" data-file-height=\"993\" /></a></div></div>\n\t\t\t<div class=\"gallerytext\">\n<p>12th-century lavatorium at <a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Abbey_of_St_Bavo&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"Abbey of St Bavo (page does not exist)\">Abbey of St Bavo</a>, <a href=\"/wiki/Ghent\" title=\"Ghent\">Ghent</a>\n</p>\n\t\t\t</div>\n\t\t</div></li>\n\t\t<li class=\"gallerybox\" style=\"width: 155px\"><div style=\"width: 155px\">\n\t\t\t<div class=\"thumb\" style=\"width: 150px;\"><div style=\"margin:15px auto;\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Thoronet_Lavabo.JPG\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/f/ff/Thoronet_Lavabo.JPG/90px-Thoronet_Lavabo.JPG\" width=\"90\" height=\"120\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/f/ff/Thoronet_Lavabo.JPG/135px-Thoronet_Lavabo.JPG 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/f/ff/Thoronet_Lavabo.JPG/180px-Thoronet_Lavabo.JPG 2x\" data-file-width=\"2304\" data-file-height=\"3072\" /></a></div></div>\n\t\t\t<div class=\"gallerytext\">\n<p>12th-century lavatorium at <a href=\"/wiki/Le_Thoronet_Abbey\" title=\"Le Thoronet Abbey\">Le Thoronet Abbey</a>\n</p>\n\t\t\t</div>\n\t\t</div></li>\n\t\t<li class=\"gallerybox\" style=\"width: 155px\"><div style=\"width: 155px\">\n\t\t\t<div class=\"thumb\" style=\"width: 150px;\"><div style=\"margin:15px auto;\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Rueda_-_Claustro_-_Lavatorio_con_sala_de_calefacci%C3%B3n_al_fondo.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/e/e7/Rueda_-_Claustro_-_Lavatorio_con_sala_de_calefacci%C3%B3n_al_fondo.jpg/90px-Rueda_-_Claustro_-_Lavatorio_con_sala_de_calefacci%C3%B3n_al_fondo.jpg\" width=\"90\" height=\"120\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/e/e7/Rueda_-_Claustro_-_Lavatorio_con_sala_de_calefacci%C3%B3n_al_fondo.jpg/135px-Rueda_-_Claustro_-_Lavatorio_con_sala_de_calefacci%C3%B3n_al_fondo.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/e/e7/Rueda_-_Claustro_-_Lavatorio_con_sala_de_calefacci%C3%B3n_al_fondo.jpg/180px-Rueda_-_Claustro_-_Lavatorio_con_sala_de_calefacci%C3%B3n_al_fondo.jpg 2x\" data-file-width=\"768\" data-file-height=\"1024\" /></a></div></div>\n\t\t\t<div class=\"gallerytext\">\n<p>13th-century lavatorium at <a href=\"/wiki/Rueda_Abbey\" title=\"Rueda Abbey\">Rueda Abbey</a>\n</p>\n\t\t\t</div>\n\t\t</div></li>\n\t\t<li class=\"gallerybox\" style=\"width: 155px\"><div style=\"width: 155px\">\n\t\t\t<div class=\"thumb\" style=\"width: 150px;\"><div style=\"margin:15px auto;\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Maulbronn_Kloster_Kreuzgang_Brunnenhaus_5.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/c/c9/Maulbronn_Kloster_Kreuzgang_Brunnenhaus_5.jpg/90px-Maulbronn_Kloster_Kreuzgang_Brunnenhaus_5.jpg\" width=\"90\" height=\"120\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/c/c9/Maulbronn_Kloster_Kreuzgang_Brunnenhaus_5.jpg/135px-Maulbronn_Kloster_Kreuzgang_Brunnenhaus_5.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/c/c9/Maulbronn_Kloster_Kreuzgang_Brunnenhaus_5.jpg/180px-Maulbronn_Kloster_Kreuzgang_Brunnenhaus_5.jpg 2x\" data-file-width=\"1536\" data-file-height=\"2048\" /></a></div></div>\n\t\t\t<div class=\"gallerytext\">\n<p>14th-century lavatorium at <a href=\"/wiki/Maulbronn_Monastery\" title=\"Maulbronn Monastery\">Maulbronn Monastery</a>, exterior\n</p>\n\t\t\t</div>\n\t\t</div></li>\n\t\t<li class=\"gallerybox\" style=\"width: 155px\"><div style=\"width: 155px\">\n\t\t\t<div class=\"thumb\" style=\"width: 150px;\"><div style=\"margin:15px auto;\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Maulbronn_Kloster_Kreuzgang_Brunnenhaus_Innen_Brunnen_2.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/a/af/Maulbronn_Kloster_Kreuzgang_Brunnenhaus_Innen_Brunnen_2.jpg/90px-Maulbronn_Kloster_Kreuzgang_Brunnenhaus_Innen_Brunnen_2.jpg\" width=\"90\" height=\"120\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/a/af/Maulbronn_Kloster_Kreuzgang_Brunnenhaus_Innen_Brunnen_2.jpg/135px-Maulbronn_Kloster_Kreuzgang_Brunnenhaus_Innen_Brunnen_2.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/a/af/Maulbronn_Kloster_Kreuzgang_Brunnenhaus_Innen_Brunnen_2.jpg/180px-Maulbronn_Kloster_Kreuzgang_Brunnenhaus_Innen_Brunnen_2.jpg 2x\" data-file-width=\"1536\" data-file-height=\"2048\" /></a></div></div>\n\t\t\t<div class=\"gallerytext\">\n<p>Maulbronn Monastery lavatorium, interior\n</p>\n\t\t\t</div>\n\t\t</div></li>\n\t\t<li class=\"gallerybox\" style=\"width: 155px\"><div style=\"width: 155px\">\n\t\t\t<div class=\"thumb\" style=\"width: 150px;\"><div style=\"margin:15px auto;\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Caen_abbayeauxdames_lavatorium_est.JPG\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/82/Caen_abbayeauxdames_lavatorium_est.JPG/90px-Caen_abbayeauxdames_lavatorium_est.JPG\" width=\"90\" height=\"120\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/82/Caen_abbayeauxdames_lavatorium_est.JPG/135px-Caen_abbayeauxdames_lavatorium_est.JPG 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/82/Caen_abbayeauxdames_lavatorium_est.JPG/180px-Caen_abbayeauxdames_lavatorium_est.JPG 2x\" data-file-width=\"2304\" data-file-height=\"3072\" /></a></div></div>\n\t\t\t<div class=\"gallerytext\">\n<p>Lavatorium at <a href=\"/wiki/Abbey_of_Sainte-Trinit%C3%A9,_Caen\" title=\"Abbey of Sainte-Trinit\u00e9, Caen\">Abbaye aux Dames</a> in <a href=\"/wiki/Caen\" title=\"Caen\">Caen</a>\n</p>\n\t\t\t</div>\n\t\t</div></li>\n</ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"See_also\">See also</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Lavatorium&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" title=\"Edit section: See also\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li><a href=\"/wiki/Lavatory_(disambiguation)\" class=\"mw-redirect mw-disambig\" title=\"Lavatory (disambiguation)\">lavatory</a></li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Lavatorium&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"reflist columns references-column-width\" style=\"-moz-column-width: 30em; -webkit-column-width: 30em; column-width: 30em; list-style-type: decimal;\">\n<ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-1\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://books.google.com/books?id=tuk-AAAAYAAJ&amp;pg=PA191&amp;dq=%22A+small+building+in+a+monastery,+in+which+the+monks+washed+their+hands+before+and+aftera+repast.+%22+An+Illustrated+Dictionary+of+Words+Used+in+Art+and+Archaeology%22&amp;hl=en&amp;sa=X&amp;ei=afigUIWoL6n5igKej4CwCQ&amp;ved=0CDIQ6AEwAA#v=onepage&amp;q&amp;f=false\">\"Lavatorium\"</a>, John William Mollett, <i>An Illustrated Dictionary of Words Used in Art and Arch\u00e6ology: Explaining Terms Frequently Used in Works on Architecture, Arms, Bronzes, Christian Art, Colour, Costume, Decoration, Devices, Emblems, Heraldry, Lace, Personal Ornaments, Pottery, Painting, Sculpture, &amp;c, with their Derivations</i>, London: Sampson Low, Marston, Searle, and Rivington, 1883, <a href=\"/wiki